                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.951,
                                "byte_start": 89961,
                                "byte_stop": 129772,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has our opinion this morning in case 06-5754, Rita versus United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.951,
                        "stop": 192.993,
                        "byte_start": 129772,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.951,
                                "stop": 22.863,
                                "byte_start": 129772,
                                "byte_stop": 181494,
                                "text": "Under our decision in United States versus Booker, the Federal Court appeals or to review federal sentences and set aside those that they find unreasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.863,
                                "stop": 25.191,
                                "byte_start": 181494,
                                "byte_stop": 190794,
                                "text": "That\u2019s basically the standard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.191,
                                "stop": 45.856,
                                "byte_start": 190794,
                                "byte_stop": 273445,
                                "text": "Several Circuits have held that when they do that they should presume that a sentence that the District Judge imposed within the properly calculated the United States Sentencing Guideline Range, they should assume that within guideline range sentence is a reasonable sentence so it\u2019s okay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.856,
                                "stop": 56.628,
                                "byte_start": 273445,
                                "byte_stop": 316495,
                                "text": "Now we granted certiorari to consider whether such a presumption is legally permissible and we conclude that it is."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.628,
                                "stop": 65.08,
                                "byte_start": 316495,
                                "byte_stop": 350350,
                                "text": "The presumption of reasonableness reflects the fact that by the time an Appeals Court is considering a within guideline sentence on review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.08,
                                "stop": 75.426,
                                "byte_start": 350350,
                                "byte_stop": 391728,
                                "text": "Both the sentencing judge and the sentencing commission will have reached the same conclusion about the proper sentence in that particular case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.426,
                                "stop": 82.748,
                                "byte_start": 391728,
                                "byte_stop": 420985,
                                "text": "That doubled determination significantly increases the likelihood that the sentence is a reasonable one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.748,
                                "stop": 93.703,
                                "byte_start": 420985,
                                "byte_stop": 464870,
                                "text": "Moreover, the sentencing statute envisions that both the sentencing judge and the commission will carryout the same basic statutory objectives."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.703,
                                "stop": 97.382,
                                "byte_start": 464870,
                                "byte_stop": 479499,
                                "text": "The judge will do that by focusing on the case at hand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.382,
                                "stop": 103.765,
                                "byte_start": 479499,
                                "byte_stop": 505099,
                                "text": "The commission will do that by looking at large numbers of sentences in similar cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.765,
                                "stop": 123.726,
                                "byte_start": 505099,
                                "byte_stop": 584929,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals reasonableness presumptions simply recognizes that real world circumstance when judges\u2019 discretionary decision is the same as the commission\u2019s view of the appropriate sentence in that kind of case it is probable that the sentence is reasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.726,
                                "stop": 133.131,
                                "byte_start": 584929,
                                "byte_stop": 622545,
                                "text": "We add that in our view the Appellate Court\u2019s use of the presumption ordinarily does not violate the Sixth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.131,
                                "stop": 162.264,
                                "byte_start": 622545,
                                "byte_stop": 739052,
                                "text": "We add further that the sentencing judge in this case explained his reasons for his choice of sentence insufficient detail and we also find that the sentencing judge here adequately explained to the defendant that he might apply a guideline sentence, he might depart within the departure framework that the guidelines create or he could treat the guidelines as advisory and decide not to apply them at all."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.264,
                                "stop": 175.099,
                                "byte_start": 739052,
                                "byte_stop": 790461,
                                "text": "For all these reasons and for other reasons that we set forth in our opinion we affirm the Court of Appeals which in turn in respect to sentencing affirm the District Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.099,
                                "stop": 181.223,
                                "byte_start": 790461,
                                "byte_stop": 814911,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed concurring opinion which Justice Ginsburg joins in part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.223,
                                "stop": 192.993,
                                "byte_start": 814911,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment in which Justice Thomas has joined and Justice Souter has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
